SECURITY REQUIREMENTS (CRITICAL):
- Move Gemini API key server-side (currently exposed in client code - CRITICAL FIX)
- Implement proper JWT authentication with refresh tokens
- Rate limiting on all endpoints
- Row Level Security (RLS) policies on all Supabase tables
- Encrypted storage (no sensitive data in localStorage)
- HTTPS everywhere
- Input validation and sanitization
- PCI-DSS compliance for payment processing
- GDPR/CCPA compliance for user data
- Content moderation: AI image analysis, manual review queue, community reporting, strike system (3 strikes = ban)
- Seller verification: ID + phone verification
- Escrow payment system for transactions

AWS INFRASTRUCTURE:
- Lambda for serverless functions (scrapers, AI processing, notifications)
- DynamoDB for high-throughput data (analytics events, sessions)
- S3 for image storage with CloudFront CDN
- API Gateway for REST endpoints
- Cognito for authentication (backup to Supabase)
- SageMaker for ML models (price prediction, recommendation engine)
- Step Functions for workflow orchestration (order processing, content generation)
- EventBridge for scheduled tasks (daily scrapers, price monitors)
- SES for transactional email
- SNS for push notifications
- CloudWatch for monitoring and alerting
- WAF for web application firewall
- Budget: $200-1600/month acceptable for enterprise-grade infrastructure

